law.text: The chief clerk of each house shall furnish a correct journal of its proceedings for each day to the Legislative Research Commission as soon as the journal is approved by the house. The Legislative Research Commission shall carefully compare or have compared the proofs of the journals.
law.history: Amended 1984 Ky. Acts ch. 111,sec. 3,effective July 13, 1984. -- Created 1956 Ky. Acts ch. 1, sec. 1.
